band_list.conductor_bio:
T.J Faur received his Bachelor of Arts Degree from Northwestern Illinois University in 1991and his Master's degree in Music Education from Butler University in 1995. T.J. studied trumpet under Leon Rapier of the Louisville Symphony and Marvin Perry of the Indianapolis Symphony.

Mr. Faur taught in Batesville, IN for three years before moving to Fort Wayne where he taught college courses at Indiana University-Purdue University Fort Wayne. He then worked at Manchester College for six years as Director of Instrumental Studies and later as the Jazz Band Director;

T.J has spent 15 years studying and working at the Interlochen Arts Camp. He was formerly Fine Arts Director and Band Director at Lakewood Park Christian School in Auburn, IN. T.J is an active cornet/trumpet performer and is in his eighth year as music conductor of the Old Crown Brass Band.
